---
description: Apply clean code principles in all Python files. Use for code quality enforcement.
globs: src/**/*.py, tests/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

Naming:
- Functions and variables: `snake_case`
- Classes: `PascalCase`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Private: prefix with `_`

Functions:
- Max 20 lines per function (aim for 10)
- Single responsibility — one function, one purpose
- Max 3 parameters; use dataclass/Pydantic model for more
- Return early to avoid deep nesting

Classes:
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Keep `__init__` minimal — delegate to factory methods if complex
- Use `@property` for computed attributes

Avoid:
- Mutable default arguments (`def f(x=[])`)
- Bare `except:` — always catch specific exceptions
- Magic numbers — use named constants
- Comments that restate the code
